event_name: 1994: Netscape browser for Windows 95. Yahoo was created
1995: Amazon.com, Craigslist and eBay go live
1998: The Google search engine is born, IPv6
2000: Peer-to-peer file sharing with Napster. First large-scale denial-of-service attacks
2003: Myspace, Skype and the Safari Web browser debut. Launch of WordPress
2004: Facebook goes online and the era of social networking begins
2013: Edward Snowden reveals that the NSA is monitoring communications.
2016: Smart deviced like Alexa, Siri and Google Home
